## 3. License Types

The following license types are defined in BNT’s standard licensing framework.  
For this project, the applicable license types are explicitly marked.

```text
[ ] PERSONAL USE – Rights Managed – Personal Use (RM-PU)  
[x] PERSONAL USE – Donation-based License  
[x] COMMERCIAL USE – Perpetual  
[x] COMMERCIAL USE – Subscription  
[ ] COMMERCIAL USE – Rights Managed – Commercial Use (RM-CU)  
[ ] COMMERCIAL USE – Rights Managed – Editorial Use (RM-EU)  
[ ] COMMERCIAL USE – Rights Managed – Retail Use (RM-RU)
```

### 3.1 Personal Use – Rights Managed – Personal Use (RM-PU)

This project does not use RM-PU as the primary license. The RM-PU model remains part of the BNT framework and may be referenced for compatibility with other BNT assets.

Key points of RM-PU (for reference):

- Type: Rights Managed – Personal Use (RM-PU)  
- Purpose: Free for strictly personal, ad-free environments.  
- Not applicable as the main license for this toolkit unless explicitly granted in a written agreement or future revision.

### 3.2 Personal Use – Donation-based Licenses

**This license type applies to BNT MemMan Toolkit.**

- Type: Donation-based licenses (for example PayPal, Stripe, and similar platforms)  
- Purpose:  
  - Free for personal use environments, optionally supported by voluntary donations.  
- Allowed Use Cases (examples):  
  - Personal Windows 10/11 workstations and lab environments  
  - Non-commercial learning setups, private productivity workflows, and home lab automation  
- Key Conditions:  
  - Same core restrictions as rights-managed personal use (no commercial exploitation or resale).  
  - Donations do not convert the license into a commercial license.  
  - Upgrades to commercial rights require a separate commercial license agreement.  
  - Default License: One (1) installation/connection of each device kind (for example Laptop, Desktop) per user.

### 3.3 Commercial Use – Perpetual License

**This license type applies to BNT MemMan Toolkit.**

- Type: Perpetual  
- Purpose:  
  - Perpetual license with one year of updates and standard support from the date of purchase, unless otherwise stated.  
- Allowed Use Cases (examples):  
  - Windows Toolkits (commercial use for small and medium enterprises)  
  - Use on consultant laptops or company-issued workstations supporting customer projects  
- Key Conditions:  
  - Perpetual right to use the specified version of the Licensed Material in commercial environments.  
  - Updates and standard support are provided for one year from purchase; continued updates or extended support may require a maintenance or support agreement.  
  - License is non-transferable unless explicitly permitted in a written agreement.  
  - Default License: One (1) installation/connection per device (for example Server, Laptop, Desktop) per license, unless otherwise agreed in writing.

### 3.4 Commercial Use – Subscription License

**This license type applies to BNT MemMan Toolkit.**

- Type: Subscription  
- Purpose:  
  - Time-bound subscription providing access, updates, and priority support for the Licensed Material.  
- Allowed Use Cases (examples):  
  - Windows Toolkits (commercial use for teams and departments)  
  - Managed service providers using the toolkit as part of internal operations (not as a resellable SaaS)  
- Key Conditions:  
  - Access to updates and priority support continues as long as the subscription remains active and paid.  
  - Upon subscription lapse, access to new updates and priority support ceases. Existing binaries or scripts may remain usable under the last valid license terms, subject to any specific agreement or restrictions.  
  - License is non-transferable unless explicitly permitted in a written agreement.  
  - Default License: One (1) installation/connection per user/device (for example Laptop, Desktop, Server, User) per license.

### 3.5 Commercial Use – Rights Managed – Commercial Use (RM-CU)

Not selected for this toolkit by default.

- Type: Rights Managed – Commercial Use (RM-CU)  
- Purpose:  
  - Tailored commercial licensing for BNT assets used in client-specific solutions, enterprise workflows, or high-value deployments with negotiated scope, duration, and support.  
- Use Cases:  
  - Embedding BNT toolkits into internal enterprise workflows or managed offerings  
- Key Conditions:  
  - Terms defined via a dedicated written agreement or order form.  
  - Default License: Defined per agreement, not applied here by default.

### 3.6 Commercial Use – Rights Managed – Editorial Use (RM-EU)

Not selected for this toolkit by default.

### 3.7 Commercial Use – Rights Managed – Retail Use (RM-RU)

Not selected for this toolkit by default.

